FIX: In /app/frontend/src/pages/NewAllocation.jsx add a debounced useEffect that watches [bankCsv, invCsv] and calls detectHeaders() after ~400ms of inactivity. Example:

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!bankCsv.trim() && !invCsv.trim()) return;
    const t = setTimeout(() => { detectHeaders(); }, 400);
    return () => clearTimeout(t);
  }, [bankCsv, invCsv]);

Alternatively trigger on each individual textarea change. The detectHeaders function itself works correctly (verified by clicking the manual Auto-detect button — selects populated immediately).
